lead_paragraph: KATHLEEN BROWN, California's state treasurer, came to New York this week to meet with officials of bond-rating agencies, financiers, bankers and Wall Street executives, shuttling from one discussion of the fiscal status of her state to another. But while she was talking about California's economy, she was also meeting and greeting people who might be instrumental in political forays. Her appearance seemed a breath of fresh political air to a group of executive and financial women who gathered yesterday morning in Ellen Chesler's apartment at the Dakota.
